Our investments internationally continue to be our fruit with outstanding growth outside of North America, and on the cost and expense side, the scale we\xe2\x80\x99ve achieved really showed its value in our margin performance. From a strategic perspective, we\xe2\x80\x99ve also seen positive development. As use of the Internet continues to evolve, we\xe2\x80\x99ve demonstrated that Akamai\xe2\x80\x99s massively distributed approach is a best way and in many case, the only way to deliver on the promise of business online.
One clear trend we\xe2\x80\x99re seeing is that the Internet is becoming more attractive medium for delivery of video, the rich media. We\xe2\x80\x99ve continued to see exciting signs in this area with this year\xe2\x80\x99s March Madness on Demand is yet another example. The event was bigger than ever, but perhaps even more promising this year many users watched a TV quality stream. 
Over half the on-line audience view these high quality videos streams, a significant data point highlighting users increased expectations for HD video online, as well as their ability to consume higher quality formats. As the demand for quality increases, and as more and more video moves on line, the performance and scale delivered by Akamai\xe2\x80\x99s massively distributed network, we become even more critical to our customer success. 
Another important development is the emergence of a growing set of new IP connected mobile devices. This creates a new source of demand for content and applications over the Internet and new challenges for delivering that content. With mobile devices it\xe2\x80\x99s critical that the last mile connectivity be optimized for each handset\xe2\x80\x99s capability, and to do that we believe the content and applications must be delivered from the edge of the cloud closer to the user. 
We\xe2\x80\x99ve been working for some time with most of the major players in the mobile space, including the largest device manufacturers, network operators and content providers.
We\xe2\x80\x99re supporting a host of very innovative mobile video and other applications, including video streaming to iPhones for some of the most popular cell phone media sites, as well as custom designed iPhone delivery for customer such as Fox News and Fox business.
Another great example in this space is research in motion, RIM, with whom we\xe2\x80\x99ve been working for many years. We recently expanded our relationship to include optimization in delivering of the new BlackBerry App World store, which leverages our secure dynamic site accelerator solution to deliver applications to Blackberries.
A third key trend is that websites are becoming more dynamic and personalized and more and more so than never, whether it\xe2\x80\x99s social media interactivity, personalized e-commerce experiences or entire B2B applications moving online. And while all of this is happening, end-users continue to expect superior performance and reliability.
In the e-commerce space for example, performance is a top priority. And most important aspect of a websites performance is how well the dynamic individualized interactions perform. This isn\xe2\x80\x99t simply about cashing; it\xe2\x80\x99s about managing a completely dynamic experience such as sign on, shopping cards, recommendation engines and so on.
For dynamic site acceleration to work, we believe that you must be at the edge of the Internet, beyond the bottleneck from the peering point in the middle mile with a great performance. That\xe2\x80\x99s why we built our massively distributed network of tens of thousands of servers and almost a 1,000 networks across 70 countries. That\xe2\x80\x99s why today Akamai serves 85 of the top100 e-commerce sites.
A recent PSA deal at arrays in Singapore is a great example of the value of our dynamic solutions. And an example of the strong relationships we\xe2\x80\x99re developing with our AsiaPac customer base. We recently signed a multi-year deal to support airasia.com which attracts over 1 million unique visitors a month.
That number increases during promotions. Arrays we use in Akamai to accelerate the online transactions that they depend on to build market share and enhance their brand. Of course, this whole discussion about cloud computing, a hot topic in the industry today, really builds on these trends. If the idea of dynamic, adaptive computing capabilities in the cloud and this is an idea that we\xe2\x80\x99ve been talking about at Akamai since we started more than 10 years ago.
We\xe2\x80\x99re already delivering on much of the promise of cloud computing with our edge computing offerings, which we introduced almost six years ago. This is where we host and deliver applications from the Akamai cloud. The tens of thousands of servers we control around the world and manage like one big resource on behalf of our clients.
In addition, our Application Acceleration Solutions, which we began rolling out in 2005, are designed to offer a cloud-based solution to the majority of enterprises that want to maintain a centralized computing infrastructure and make their applications available to a globally-distributed user base. 
Our goal is to ensure that end user performance expectations are met regardless of where an application and it\xe2\x80\x99s database are hosted. As our clients evolve more and more to take advantage of cloud computing, we\xe2\x80\x99re continuing to invest in even more advanced solutions to help them realize the full potential of network computing over the Internet. 
